## Claude Code adapter

This entrypoint is explicitly for Claude Code. Do not detect, infer, or switch hosts at runtime.

### Repository instructions and paths

The applicable `CLAUDE.md` hierarchy and `.claude/rules` are binding repository instructions. Read `AGENTS.md` when present for useful conventions and intent, but it is not a Claude Code instruction surface unless higher-level instructions explicitly make it one.

`${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}` is `<skill-root>`. Use it for bundled scripts and references regardless of the repository working directory.

### Read-only workers

Use `Agent` with the built-in `Explore` type for parallel audit and cold plan review. Explore is read-only, but workers do not receive this skill or the parent's conversation automatically; repeat the applicable repository rules and full worker contract in every prompt. Preserve the parent model unless the user explicitly requests another Claude model. Queue work beyond the available host capacity.

### Execute

After the shared preflight succeeds, run:

```text
bash ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/scripts/create-execution-worktree.sh <repo-root> <full-planned-sha> <plan-id> -- <in-scope-path>...
```

Use `EnterWorktree` with the returned existing worktree path. Then dispatch one foreground `general-purpose` Agent in that worktree without requesting a second isolation layer. Inline the complete plan and executor preamble. Default the executor to the Claude-native `sonnet` alias; an explicit user-supplied Claude model overrides it.

For revision feedback, use `SendMessage` to the same agent. After review, return to the original checkout with `ExitWorktree` while retaining the executor branch/worktree for the user. Update the plan index only after returning to the original checkout.

If `EnterWorktree`, `Agent`, the returned worktree path, or `SendMessage` is unavailable, stop and hand over the plan manually. Do not fall back to a fresh default-base worktree.
